      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Apothecary_Slide1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:1f12051013ecfeb2</T>
      <T n="text">0xD89A8A0B<!--The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Skill</b></font> allows Sims to craft a variety of Elixirs that cure <font color="#199C2C"><b>Ailments</b></font>, provide flexible ways to care for Needs, Emotions, <font color="#199C2C"><b>Balance</b></font>, and even manage Fears.\n\nSims can consume these to get the effects themselves, but also <font color="#199C2C"><b>Give Elixirs</b></font> to other Sims which will then trigger those effects for the target—whether it be something beneficial or...not. Find this social under the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary</b></font> category.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Apothecary_Slide2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:1f12051013ecfeb1</T>
      <T n="text">0x99460FD8<!--Elixirs can be crafted at any <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Table</b></font>. Sims can find these tables around the world of Innisgreen, but they may also be purchased from <font color="#199C2C"><b>Build Mode</b></font>. Luck Charms may also be crafted here at Level 7.\n\nSome ingredients can be purchased directly from an Apothecary Table, but others may need to be acquired by other means. Lightning Root Leaves, Aura Petals, and any herbs or flowers may be Gardened. Other ingredients may be Foraged for at Level 2 of the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Skill</b></font>. <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotion Potions</b></font> are special and need to be absorbed from other Sims—either through Fairy Abilities, or with the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Emotion Stone</b></font> which unlocks at Level 6 of the <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Skill</b></font>. They may also be acquired from a <font color="#199C2C"><b>Moody Shrub</b></font>. Starting at Level 3, Sims can convert Emotion Potions from one mood to another.--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InEP19\UI\Tutorial\EP19_Apothecary_Slide3.png">2f7d0004:00000000:1f12051013ecfeb0</T>
      <T n="text">0x87BB54ED<!--The <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Skill</b></font> can be leveled up by crafting at an <font color="#199C2C"><b>Apothecary Table</b></font>, but Sims can also purchase and read <font color="#199C2C"><b>Skill Books</b></font> from a Bookshelf, research on a Computer, or by consuming <font color="#199C2C"><b>Cures</b></font> that have been crafted.--></T>
    </U>
